               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>Pap ; 6 x 2 cm</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">A strip of papyrus from the horizontal center of a column which probably made up of a roll.  Between 5 and 8 letters are preserved from each line. The papyrus is medium-brown in color, and rather coarse and thick. It has a double horizontal layer and is probbaly from the overlap of a kollesis. The ink is black.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">11 lines</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: Recto</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Upper margin is 1.3 cm.  Only one hand is distinguishable. It is small (3 mm high) and clear, a rounded and elegant uncial. The letters are carefully separated with almost no cursive characteristics. Very few letters extend above or below the line. No stops or other diacritical marks are in evidence. dated in the IIIrd A.D.; cf. P.Oxy. III 412 = Roberts 22a (III A.D.)</p>
                  </handDesc>
               </physDesc>
